[[uk:КатегоріяСпільноти]]
One of the best ways to learn more about Emacs is to get to know other people who use and customize Emacs. Here are a few resources for doing so.

* EmacsForums -- web forums about Emacs
* EmacsMailingLists -- often also available as newsgroups
* EmacsNewsgroups -- beginner-focused, general, and technical discussions
* EmacsScreencasts
* EmacsPodcasts
* EmacsConf -- next one is Nov 27-28, 2021; details at https://emacsconf.org/2021/
* EmacsStackExchange -- technical Emacs questions and answers
* [[InternetRelayChat|IRC]] (Internet Relay Chat) -- real-time discussion, EmacsChannel in particular
* [[Usergroups]] -- Emacs user groups and meetups all over the world.
* %%EmacsWiki%% [[CategoryHomepage|Homepages]] -- home pages of Emacs friends, including '''you!'''
* EmacsDiversity
* EmacsCoaching
* EmacsMastodon

Links to other sites:

* [https://planet.emacslife.com Planet Emacslife] -- an aggregator of Emacs-related blogs
* [https://sachachua.com/blog/category/emacs-news Emacs News] -- a weekly newsletter
* [https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs Emacs Reddit] One of the most popular Emacs communities online.
* [https://twitter.com/hashtag/emacs #emacs on Twitter]
* [https://emacs.ch emacs.ch] - an Emacs-focused Mastodon instance
